- I think so.

247
00:18:48.573 --> 00:18:49.573
Come on.

248
00:18:50.296 --> 00:18:51.731
Popcorn? Why Popcorn?

249
00:18:51.831 --> 00:18:54.281
Because they're clowns. that's why.

250
00:19:28.701 --> 00:19:30.259
Mike. get me of here!

251
00:19:37.076 --> 00:19:39.666
Hurry. they're coming!

252
00:20:10.343 --> 00:20:11.923
We have to tell the police.

253
00:20:12.023 --> 00:20:14.636
Oh yeah. we'll go right into the station
and tell them there's a bunch of clowns...

254
00:20:14.736 --> 00:20:16.865
...running around in the hills and killing you
with cotton candy?

255
00:20:16.965 --> 00:20:20.532
I have a friend there.
I know he'll believe us.

256
00:20:20.632 --> 00:20:23.852
I do not know. Deb.
I wouldn't even believe us.

257
00:20:24.490 --> 00:20:26.481
Crescent Cove - 5 miles

258
00:20:34.132 --> 00:20:35.632
Come brother.

259
00:21:01.560 --> 00:21:02.822
What the hell?

260
00:21:12.204 --> 00:21:14.656
Dave! Oh my God!
Something horrible has happened!

261
00:21:14.756 --> 00:21:17.436
- Somebody has been killed!
- Wait a second. Debbie. What happened?

262
00:21:17.557 --> 00:21:19.865
You've gotta help us!
We've gotta do something! 2 people dead!

263
00:21:19.965 --> 00:21:20.917
Who. Debbie. who's dead?

264
00:21:21.017 --> 00:21:23.265
- Joe Lombardo. He's dead.
- And some old man. too.

265
00:21:23.365 --> 00:21:24.983
Wait a second. guys.
Are you sure about this?

266
00:21:25.083 --> 00:21:28.669
Yes. you idiot! They were hanging there wrapped
up in these cotton candy things...

267
00:21:28.769 --> 00:21:30.551
...these... cocoons.

268
00:21:30.690 --> 00:21:32.681
- Cocoons?
- Yes. cocoons.

269
00:21:32.925 --> 00:21:36.007
- You know. cocoons.
- Alright everybody. calm down.

270
00:21:36.107 --> 00:21:38.197
Look Debbie. come inside and explain this to me.

271
00:21:38.297 --> 00:21:44.317
I'd like to help you. but before I can
I got to understand what's going on here myself.

272
00:21:51.610 --> 00:21:53.100
Drugstore

273
00:21:54.847 --> 00:21:58.178
<i>I really need this new makeup. </i>

274
00:21:58.278 --> 00:22:00.775
<i>- Okay. I'll buy some over</i>
<i>there at the drugstore. - Good.</i>

275
00:22:00.875 --> 00:22:03.109
Okay? And then we'll go on.

276
00:22:04.890 --> 00:22:05.890
Oh. look.

277
00:22:12.732 --> 00:22:13.732
Cute.

278
00:22:22.174 --> 00:22:23.434
Alright. sit down.

279
00:22:24.376 --> 00:22:26.546
Let's start from the beginning.

280
00:22:27.747 --> 00:22:30.098
<i>Okay. We were at The Top of the World... </i></i>

281
00:22:30.198 --> 00:22:33.719
...and then we saw that shooting star
and we decided to go look for it.

282
00:22:33.819 --> 00:22:37.456
But instead of finding the shooting star.
we saw this circus tent.

283
00:22:37.556 --> 00:22:40.351
And that's when we went inside and that is
where we saw those people...

284
00:22:40.451 --> 00:22:42.996
...in those pink
cotton candy cocoons.

285
00:22:43.295 --> 00:22:46.599
Dave. it was not a circus tent.
It was something else.

286
00:22:46.699 --> 00:22:48.467
- What? What?
<i>- It was a spaceship.</i>

287
00:22:48.567 --> 00:22:51.115
...and there were these things.
these- these killer clowns...

288
00:22:51.215 --> 00:22:54.995
<i>... and then they shot popcorn at us.
We barely escaped. </i>

289
00:22:57.042 --> 00:22:59.670
Killer clowns from outer space?

290
00:23:00.379 --> 00:23:01.846
Holy shit.

291
00:23:02.047 --> 00:23:05.251
Dave. we are telling you the truth.
You gotta believe us.

292
00:23:05.351 --> 00:23:06.852
Let me tell you something. honey.

293
00:23:06.952 --> 00:23:09.789
I was just over there.
There's nothing goin' on.

294
00:23:09.889 --> 00:23:12.425
Excuse me please.
but we are talking to Dave.

295
00:23:12.525 --> 00:23:16.328
Now just hold on a second. Mooney. They say that
some people are dead. Let's hear them out.

296
00:23:16.428 --> 00:23:17.554
Alright. Dave...

297
00:23:18.464 --> 00:23:19.464
Okay.

298
00:23:19.598 --> 00:23:21.429
Clowns. cotton candy...

299
00:23:21.567 --> 00:23:23.194
...flying popcorn.

300
00:23:23.435 --> 00:23:26.806
Go ahead. Let us make fools
out of the police department.

301
00:23:26.906 --> 00:23:28.099
I told you I was
just over there!

302
00:23:28.199 --> 00:23:30.217
Are you gonna believe me
or this little this little tramp?

303
00:23:30.317 --> 00:23:31.507
Come on. Mooney!

304
00:23:32.211 --> 00:23:34.101
I'm handling this. alright?

305
00:23:37.316 --> 00:23:40.444
Alright. Debbie. who is your friend?

306
00:23:40.719 --> 00:23:42.888
Mike. We go to school together.

307
00:23:42.988 --> 00:23:45.858
You two were
<i>On Top of the World together?</i>

308
00:23:46.425 --> 00:23:47.425
Yeah.

309
00:23:48.661 --> 00:23:50.720
I know you. you little fart.

310
00:23:51.163 --> 00:23:53.893
You hang out with the Terenzi brothers.

311
00:23:54.600 --> 00:23:56.966
Clowns? I get it.

312
00:23:57.469 --> 00:23:59.016
Another one of their stupid stunts

313
00:23:59.116 --> 00:24:02.742
...to sell ice cream from that goddamn
truck that hoodlums run around in.

314
00:24:02.842 --> 00:24:04.610
Well. now I really believe this.

315
00:24:04.710 --> 00:24:06.595
You better go now. Dave.

316
00:24:06.695 --> 00:24:08.394
...before the clowns take over. huh?

317
00:24:08.494 --> 00:24:10.629
And when you get back from savin' the world.

318
00:24:10.729 --> 00:24:15.586
...I want a full written report so I can give it
to the chief when he comes back on Monday morning.

319
00:24:16.856 --> 00:24:19.291
Look. everything happened
just the way we said.

320
00:24:19.391 --> 00:24:21.026
We are telling you the truth!

321
00:24:21.126 --> 00:24:23.786
Alright. alright.
You two come with me.

322
00:24:24.396 --> 00:24:25.377
Come on.

323
00:24:25.477 --> 00:24:28.934
Hurry up. Dave.
Don't let 'em get away...

324
00:24:29.034 --> 00:24:30.467
Go ahead. Dave...

325
00:24:31.604 --> 00:24:33.634
Make a dummy out of yourself!

326
00:24:34.773 --> 00:24:37.503
But you're not making
a dummy out of me.

327
00:24:39.712 --> 00:24:41.392
You. in the back.

328
00:25:54.905 --> 00:25:56.705
Uh... oh!

329
00:26:11.503 --> 00:26:12.731
Uh... excuse me...

330
00:26:13.305 --> 00:26:14.845
Oh. my...

331
00:26:15.240 --> 00:26:16.639
How can I help you?

332
00:26:23.571 --> 00:26:24.771
Oh no!

333
00:26:52.177 --> 00:26:54.259
Alright. I'm going up
there and check this out.

334
00:26:54.359 --> 00:26:55.848
First I'm taking you home.

335
00:26:55.948 --> 00:27:00.286
No way. I'm going up there with you.
You can't tell me what to do.

336
00:27:00.386 --> 00:27:01.823
Debbie. just listen to me. will you?

337
00:27:01.923 --> 00:27:03.856
I don't have to listen to you.

338
00:27:03.956 --> 00:27:06.458
You're not my boyfriend any more. alright?

339
00:27:06.558 --> 00:27:09.261
That's true.
I'm not your boyfriend any more.

340
00:27:09.361 --> 00:27:11.630
That doesn't change
the way I feel for you. Debbie

341
00:27:11.730 --> 00:27:13.254
Dave. please.

342
00:27:13.665 --> 00:27:15.633
Don't do this to me.

343
00:27:16.135 --> 00:27:17.970
Alright Debbie. you got a choice.

344
00:27:18.070 --> 00:27:21.455
You either go home or I take you back to
the station and lock you up for safety.

345
00:27:21.555 --> 00:27:23.755
How's that?

346
00:27:26.741 --> 00:27:27.941
Pizza.

347
00:27:28.741 --> 00:27:29.741
Oh...

348
00:27:30.949 --> 00:27:32.890
- Pizza.
- Uh-huh.

349
00:27:50.255 --> 00:27:51.255
Oh?

350
00:27:52.104 --> 00:27:53.366
For me?

351
00:27:58.143 --> 00:27:59.940
Aw Jim.
is this from you?

352
00:28:10.889 --> 00:28:12.083
Look. Debbie...

353
00:28:12.491 --> 00:28:14.941
May I please speak to Mike outside?

354
00:28:16.428 --> 00:28:18.020
Right. Sure.

355
00:28:19.398 --> 00:28:20.398
Thank you.

356
00:28:29.341 --> 00:28:32.981
- Your old boyfriend? This is great.
- You come here?

357
00:28:34.947 --> 00:28:37.216
Probably taking me on top
of the hill and shoot me.

358
00:28:37.316 --> 00:28:39.363
Well. don't worry about Dave.

359
00:28:39.463 --> 00:28:42.193
It's those clowns
who gotta worry about.

360
00:28:42.855 --> 00:28:46.741
Listen. as soon as you guys leave here.
I'm gonna follow you up there.

361
00:28:46.841 --> 00:28:50.696
You're gonna follow us up there?
Debbie. I don't even wanna go up there!

362
00:28:50.796 --> 00:28:53.134
Listen. you stay inside the house
and keep the door locked.

363
00:28:53.234 --> 00:28:56.083
I'll be back in a little bit and chipper.

364
00:28:56.835 --> 00:28:57.835
Okay?

365
00:28:59.571 --> 00:29:00.571
You better.

366
00:29:10.716 --> 00:29:12.206
It's good timing.

367
00:30:18.417 --> 00:30:19.543
Wait a minute.

368
00:30:20.953 --> 00:30:22.079
Where is it?

369
00:30:22.421 --> 00:30:25.522
- Yeah. that's what I'd like to know.
- It was right there where that hole is.

370
00:30:25.622 --> 00:30:27.721
So you're saying the
hole is where the tent was?

371
00:30:27.821 --> 00:30:28.813
The tent made that hole?

372
00:30:28.913 --> 00:30:31.644
Yes! It was there.
Look. we saw it. That's a fact.

373
00:30:31.744 --> 00:30:33.479
I tell you what the facts are. mister!

374
00:30:33.579 --> 00:30:36.079
You said people are being killed.
Now. where are the bodies?

375
00:30:36.179 --> 00:30:39.486
I don't know! I saw Joe Lombardo dead.
I can only tell you what I think I saw.

376
00:30:39.586 --> 00:30:41.118
<i>Oh. so now you just think you saw?</i>

377
00:30:41.218 --> 00:30:44.125
No. I know what I saw! I just can't prove it.
My proof is gone.

378
00:30:44.225 --> 00:30:45.905
Yeah right. Turn around.

379
00:30:47.079 --> 00:30:50.364
Mooney was right. got nothing
better to do but causing problems.

380
00:30:50.464 --> 00:30:54.286
- You'll not gonna get away with it this time.
- Away with what? Debbie saw it too.

381
00:30:54.386 --> 00:30:55.854
Yes. she did. didn't she?

382
00:30:55.954 --> 00:30:57.512
- Ow!
- Come on.

383
00:31:02.160 --> 00:31:05.709
- Eddie. is that a new bike you got?
<i>- What's happened. Spike?</i>

384
00:31:17.359 --> 00:31:18.359
Wooh!

385
00:31:18.710 --> 00:31:21.907
Big Bad Jojo comin' into town.

386
00:31:22.914 --> 00:31:25.417
- Watch this. babe.
- Is that bike too big for you?

387
00:31:25.517 --> 00:31:26.717
Patty!

388
00:31:30.289 --> 00:31:33.229
- Mean bike you got there.
- Yeah.

389
00:31:34.926 --> 00:31:36.450
Can I take a ride?

390
00:31:37.095 --> 00:31:38.095
Pal?

391
00:31:38.316 --> 00:31:41.033
Aww. you can't take a ride...

392
00:31:41.133 --> 00:31:42.657
Can I beep the horn?

393
00:31:46.204 --> 00:31:48.234
Oh. thank you!

394
00:31:54.313 --> 00:31:57.743
He should've let the man ride his bike.

395
00:32:01.420 --> 00:32:03.077
I'm sorry.

396
00:32:03.177 --> 00:32:05.555
I seem to have broken your bike.

397
00:32:10.829 --> 00:32:12.439
Where did he go?

398
00:32:14.900 --> 00:32:16.650
Badaboo. Badaboo!

399
00:32:26.378 --> 00:32:29.808
What are you gonna do.
knock my block off?

400
00:32:32.317 --> 00:32:33.317
Damn!

401
00:32:35.053 --> 00:32:36.955
Come on. let's get out of here!

402
00:32:37.055 --> 00:32:39.591
- Come on. guys!
- Get out of here!

403
00:32:48.967 --> 00:32:51.570
Here is more ketchup
for your french fries.

404
00:32:51.670 --> 00:32:55.618
No here is more ketchup. I want
you to sit still and eat your hamburger.

405
00:32:55.718 --> 00:32:57.976
You know. this isn't as
much fun as it used to be.

406
00:32:58.076 --> 00:33:00.596
It is if you're the winners.

407
00:34:01.173 --> 00:34:02.743
Back here. young lady.

408
00:34:02.843 --> 00:34:05.738
You're not going anywhere
'till you've finished your food.

409
00:34:25.964 --> 00:34:27.084
What's going on?

410
00:36:11.169 --> 00:36:12.359
Alright. get out.

411
00:36:16.274 --> 00:36:17.434
Turn around.

412
00:36:17.876 --> 00:36:19.444
What are you doing. man?

413
00:36:19.544 --> 00:36:21.023
You're not gonna hit me. are you?

414
00:36:21.123 --> 00:36:22.481
Just turn around. pal.
Alright.

415
00:36:22.581 --> 00:36:27.411
- Look. I'm sorry about Debbie. I didn't know...
- Just drop it. Mike!

416
00:36:30.655 --> 00:36:31.747
Check this out.

417
00:36:33.124 --> 00:36:34.386
That's the stuff!

418
00:36:34.559 --> 00:36:37.844
That's the stuff I told you about
that was wrapped all around Lombardo.

419
00:36:37.944 --> 00:36:41.233
- Where did you get that?
- In that jeep over there.

420
00:36:41.333 --> 00:36:42.498
That's McReed's jeep.

421
00:36:42.598 --> 00:36:44.402
- Who's McReed?
- Bob McReed.

422
00:36:44.502 --> 00:36:46.338
He was up here
tonight with me and Debbie.

423
00:36:46.438 --> 00:36:47.978
Those are his glasses.

424
00:36:48.540 --> 00:36:50.303
They got him. He's dead.

425
00:37:05.156 --> 00:37:06.984
Crescent Cove Police Station.
Mooney speaking.

426
00:37:07.084 --> 00:37:08.807
<i>I want to report an altercation. </i>

427
00:37:08.907 --> 00:37:11.075
Wait a minute. Calm down.
I can't understand you.

428
00:37:11.175 --> 00:37:12.445
<i> - Clowns!</i>
- What?

429
00:37:12.545 --> 00:37:15.066
<i>are at my front door</i>
<i>and destroying my property!</i>

430
00:37:15.166 --> 00:37:19.317
Clowns. huh. and now
they're at your front door.

431
00:37:19.417 --> 00:37:21.052
<i>are at my front door right now!</i>

432
00:37:21.152 --> 00:37:24.792
- Wait. Who is this?
<i>- Could you just come over here?</i>

433
00:37:25.810 --> 00:37:28.074
Stupid kids and their pranks...

434
00:37:32.684 --> 00:37:34.174
Rich little bastards.

435
00:37:35.286 --> 00:37:36.981
They shoot 'em all.

436
00:37:38.890 --> 00:37:41.484
Daddy sends them to fancy schools...

437
00:37:42.627 --> 00:37:46.267
...so the police department
can babysit them. Pricks.

438
00:37:55.040 --> 00:37:57.630
Police Station. Mooney speaking. Yup.

439
00:37:58.343 --> 00:37:59.935
Hello. Curt?

440
00:38:00.545 --> 00:38:03.673
I think I have a bit of a problem here.

441
00:38:08.054 --> 00:38:10.282
Wait a moment.

442
00:38:11.222 --> 00:38:13.392
This is not you too. Mr. Myers.

443
00:38:15.160 --> 00:38:17.578
Police Station. Mooney here.
What?

444
00:38:17.678 --> 00:38:22.167
<i> - took my wife... The clowns... </i>
- They took your wife away in a balloon?

445
00:38:22.267 --> 00:38:26.187
Well. you don't need the police.
You need a psychiatrist!

446
00:38:27.505 --> 00:38:28.767
Mr. Myers?

447
00:38:32.043 --> 00:38:35.823
The Terenzi brothers
and the whole town are in on this?

448
00:38:37.315 --> 00:38:39.442
Well. to hell with 'em all.

449
00:38:43.955 --> 00:38:45.590
If you want to play games...

450
00:38:45.690 --> 00:38:48.280
...you're messing with the wrong guy.

451
00:38:59.738 --> 00:39:01.035
Jesus! No!

452
00:39:01.239 --> 00:39:03.764
Oh no! Come on. Joe. get going!

453
00:39:10.048 --> 00:39:11.048
God!

454
00:39:22.553 --> 00:39:24.153
Woaaaah!

455
00:41:52.327 --> 00:41:53.327
Aah!

456
00:41:59.183 --> 00:42:02.164
I'll call the state police up
in Marlborough. They got a lab.

457
00:42:02.264 --> 00:42:04.733
Maybe somebody up there can
tell us what this stuff this.

458
00:42:04.833 --> 00:42:07.158
It is not cotton candy. that's for sure.

459
00:42:07.258 --> 00:42:10.548
Yes. Finally.
That's what I've been telling you.

460
00:42:12.096 --> 00:42:16.111
Look. I'm sorry I've
been a little tough on you back there.

461
00:42:16.211 --> 00:42:18.158
It's been a hard night.

462
00:42:19.437 --> 00:42:22.086
Having Debbie involved
just makes it a lot more difficult.

463
00:42:22.186 --> 00:42:23.821
What can I say? I didn't know...

464
00:42:23.921 --> 00:42:27.141
It has nothing to do with you.
really. It's me.

465
00:42:27.478 --> 00:42:30.558
Obviously she goes for laughs.
not stability.

466
00:42:42.564 --> 00:42:43.684
<i> Yoo-hoo. </i>

467
00:42:57.656 --> 00:42:59.156
Ahh! Oh!

468
00:43:01.471 --> 00:43:02.467
Boo!

469
00:43:02.567 --> 00:43:03.639
Oh my God.

470
00:43:06.518 --> 00:43:08.128
That's funny.

471
00:43:28.972 --> 00:43:30.372
Oh! Ah!

472
00:43:37.348 --> 00:43:39.964
Just drop me off here.
I'll take the bus home.

473
00:43:40.064 --> 00:43:43.494
No way.
You are the one who has seen these things.

474
00:43:44.422 --> 00:43:46.312
Look! A clown! Right there!

475
00:43:50.328 --> 00:43:52.780
There he is. I told you.
You get out there and shoot him?

476
00:43:52.880 --> 00:43:55.099
- Get him. Dave!
- Mike. just hang on.

477
00:43:55.199 --> 00:43:57.322
Calm down. Let me check this out.

478
00:44:13.251 --> 00:44:16.051
- Holy shit!
- I don't believe it.

479
00:44:22.794 --> 00:44:25.734
- Dave. run him down!
- Mike. let go! Mike!

480
00:44:29.979 --> 00:44:30.979
588

481
00:44:32.247 --> 00:44:33.738
What are you doing buddy?

482
00:44:33.838 --> 00:44:36.534
Sorry. I freaked out a little bit.

483
00:44:36.908 --> 00:44:38.398
Where is he?

484
00:44:47.018 --> 00:44:48.542
I don't know.

485
00:44:48.820 --> 00:44:50.570
I don't see him anywhere.

486
00:44:52.890 --> 00:44:53.890
He's gone.

487
00:44:54.725 --> 00:44:56.158
He went straight up.

488
00:44:57.495 --> 00:44:58.826
I've seen enough.

489
00:44:59.997 --> 00:45:02.700
One Baker five.
Curt. do you read me? Over.

490
00:45:02.800 --> 00:45:05.530
One Baker five.
This is Mooney speaking.

491
00:45:06.370 --> 00:45:08.288
I was a little worried about you.

492
00:45:08.388 --> 00:45:11.809
I thought the big bad
clowns got a hold of you. Over.

493
00:45:11.909 --> 00:45:14.361
Mooney. I want you to listen to me
and don't say anything.

494
00:45:14.461 --> 00:45:16.274
I want you to call
the state police and get help.

495
00:45:16.374 --> 00:45:19.727
<i>There are clowns
and they are killing people. Over. </i>

496
00:45:20.017 --> 00:45:21.665
Okay. let me get this straight.

497
00:45:21.765 --> 00:45:24.767
You say there are clowns
and you've seen them.

498
00:45:24.867 --> 00:45:28.986
Okay. Dave. that's it. Screw you and
your college friends.

499
00:45:29.260 --> 00:45:31.476
I've had enough from you
and from everybody else.

500
00:45:31.576 --> 00:45:35.983
I know what you guys are trying to do:
Break me down. drive me out of the force.

501
00:45:36.083 --> 00:45:38.910
Well. it's gonna take a hell
of a lot more than a lame prank like this...

502
00:45:39.010 --> 00:45:41.220
to get Curtis Mooney to throw in his badge.

503
00:45:41.320 --> 00:45:44.001
So fuck you! Over.

504
00:45:44.575 --> 00:45:48.112
- Aww shit!
- Mooney. this is an emergency. Mooney!

505
00:45:48.212 --> 00:45:51.564
He cut me off.
That son of a bitch cut me off!

506
00:45:51.664 --> 00:45:53.300
I gotta- I gotta get back to the station.

507
00:45:53.400 --> 00:45:57.305
I don't know what I gotta say.
but I have to get through to state police.

508
00:45:58.556 --> 00:46:00.536
- Get the truck!
- And the girls?

509
00:46:00.636 --> 00:46:02.543
Forget about the girls.
They eat too much.

510
00:46:02.643 --> 00:46:05.844
- It is our ice cream!
- So what? The truck's getting away!

511
00:46:05.944 --> 00:46:08.242
Those aren't killer clowns.
those are the Terenzi brothers.

512
00:46:08.342 --> 00:46:09.323
The Terenzi brothers?

513
00:46:09.423 --> 00:46:12.690
Get back to the station. radio for help. I'll
catch up with my friends and warn them.

514
00:46:12.790 --> 00:46:15.387
Alright. tell everyone to stay indoors
and don't do anything stupid.

515
00:46:15.487 --> 00:46:16.487
You too.

516
00:46:23.615 --> 00:46:25.083
<i>- You idiot!</i>
- Oh. shit.

517
00:46:25.183 --> 00:46:27.768
- Don't yell at me. You were driving.
- So now it's my fault?

518
00:46:27.868 --> 00:46:32.104
- This whole ice cream thing was your idea.
- My idea? You said we would have girls this way.

519
00:46:32.204 --> 00:46:33.270
No I didn't. You did.

520
00:46:33.370 --> 00:46:34.770
- You did.
- You did.

521
00:46:38.296 --> 00:46:39.957
Hey Rich! Paul!

522
00:46:40.064 --> 00:46:42.016
Oh man. am I glad to see you guys.

523
00:46:42.116 --> 00:46:44.136
Mike. how're you doin'?
You want some ice cream? We got-

524
00:46:44.236 --> 00:46:46.785
No man. listen. Something horrible's happened.
I need your help.

525
00:46:46.885 --> 00:46:48.487
- What are you talking about?
- What's wrong?

526
00:46:48.587 --> 00:46:53.321
There is no time to explain.
There's clowns goin' around killing people.

527
00:46:53.421 --> 00:46:54.407
Uh-huh.

528
00:46:54.507 --> 00:46:57.162
Tonight. Debbie and I were up
<i>on The Top of the World... </i>

529
00:46:57.262 --> 00:46:59.599
...and we found this spaceship
and we saw these...

530
00:46:59.699 --> 00:47:02.140
clowns and they were carrying these...
cotton candy cocoons...

531
00:47:02.240 --> 00:47:05.523
and they were shooting these..
these... popcorn guns.

532
00:47:05.623 --> 00:47:07.692
There is a circus tent-spaceship. right?

533
00:47:07.792 --> 00:47:11.229
But it's not there any more but we were
there and we saw the whole thing.

534
00:47:11.329 --> 00:47:13.714
And they say we're crazy.
So?

535
00:47:13.814 --> 00:47:15.913
Oh come on. you guys.
I am not foolin' around!

536
00:47:16.013 --> 00:47:19.082
Mike. what do you want us to do?
We have ice cream to sell tonight.

537
00:47:19.182 --> 00:47:21.084
Paul. this is more important
than selling ice cream.

538
00:47:21.184 --> 00:47:23.774
There's clowns goin' around killing people.
We're all in danger.

539
00:47:23.874 --> 00:47:25.977
Well. we have not sold
much ice cream tonight.

540
00:47:26.077 --> 00:47:29.247
- We haven't sold any.
- Come on. guys. will you help me?

541
00:47:29.347 --> 00:47:32.950
At least take me over to Debbie. okay?
I think she is in danger.

542
00:47:33.050 --> 00:47:35.075
Does she have any roommates?

543
00:47:35.586 --> 00:47:38.389
Yes. she's got two.
She's got two beautiful roommates.

544
00:47:38.489 --> 00:47:39.922
...with big boobs.

545
00:47:40.057 --> 00:47:41.667
Do they like ice cream?

546
00:47:41.826 --> 00:47:42.826
They love it.

547
00:47:43.628 --> 00:47:46.008
What are we waiting for?

548
00:47:46.731 --> 00:47:47.857
Come on!

549
00:47:49.667 --> 00:47:51.897
Let me through.
Let's get away.

550
00:47:56.674 --> 00:47:58.301
Freak yourself

551
00:47:58.976 --> 00:48:01.426
You ain't gonna get the best of me.

552
00:48:07.351 --> 00:48:12.321
I made it through Korea.
I can make it through this bullshit.

553
00:48:28.321 --> 00:48:30.771
Woop-dee-goddamn-dee-doo!

554
00:48:31.709 --> 00:48:33.438
What do we have here?

555
00:48:43.287 --> 00:48:46.484
Well son. I think you made a big mistake.

556
00:48:47.058 --> 00:48:49.288
You're in Mooney territory now.

557
00:48:51.896 --> 00:48:52.896
For me?

558
00:49:03.107 --> 00:49:07.203
I ought to shoot you right now.
you red nosed freak.

559
00:49:07.745 --> 00:49:09.838
So you wanna play games. eh?

560
00:49:20.991 --> 00:49:22.185
Turn around!

561
00:49:27.998 --> 00:49:29.329
Alright...

562
00:49:30.501 --> 00:49:32.970
I am supposed to read you your rights...

563
00:49:33.070 --> 00:49:35.380
...but you're in Mooney's jail...

564
00:49:36.374 --> 00:49:38.544
...and you ain't got no rights.

565
00:49:38.843 --> 00:49:40.743
Alright. buster.

566
00:49:41.512 --> 00:49:42.512
God.

567
00:49:51.122 --> 00:49:52.972
Hey Officer Mooney.
c'mon. let us outta here!

568
00:49:53.072 --> 00:49:55.900
- Are we gonna be here all night or what?
- Yeah. we want our phone call.

569
00:49:56.000 --> 00:49:59.477
- Right. I wanna call my...
- Shut up!

570
00:50:09.273 --> 00:50:11.104
Get your hands up.

571
00:50:33.798 --> 00:50:35.390
Get in there.

572
00:50:54.118 --> 00:50:56.008
I don't know who you are...

573
00:50:56.587 --> 00:50:58.967
...but before this night's over...

574
00:50:59.557 --> 00:51:02.147
...you're gonna be begging for mercy.

575
00:51:18.909 --> 00:51:20.570
What are you in for?

576
00:51:36.424 --> 00:51:38.594
Siren blaring. then shuts down)

577
00:51:46.136 --> 00:51:47.536
Mooney!

578
00:51:51.909 --> 00:51:53.706
Police Department. Hello?

579
00:52:47.658 --> 00:52:51.558
Mooney? Mooney. you back here?

580
00:53:43.020 --> 00:53:44.020
God.

581
00:54:30.901 --> 00:54:32.903
Hey Dave...

582
00:54:33.003 --> 00:54:36.223
Who was the girl
who I saw you with last night?

583
00:54:46.817 --> 00:54:48.409
Do not worry. Dave.

584
00:54:50.254 --> 00:54:52.449
All we wanna do is kill you.

585
00:55:45.276 --> 00:55:47.477
<i>V.C.P.D.. this is</i>
Marlborough state police. </i>

586
00:55:47.577 --> 00:55:49.817
<i>Dave. Curt. are you there? Over. </i>

587
00:55:49.947 --> 00:55:52.421
Jack. we need your assistance.
The town's gotten crazy.

588
00:55:52.521 --> 00:55:54.318
People are getting killed. Over.

589
00:55:54.418 --> 00:55:57.221
<i>What's all these reports</i>
<i>about circus clowns?</i>

590
00:55:57.321 --> 00:55:58.772
These clowns aren't people.

591
00:55:58.872 --> 00:56:01.859
They are some kind of creature.
things from another planet.

592
00:56:01.959 --> 00:56:04.928
Look Jack. they're killing people.
Officer Mooney is dead.

593
00:56:05.028 --> 00:56:07.678
I know. I saw. He was killed
by one of these things.

594
00:56:07.778 --> 00:56:11.109
Could you send all
available units immediately please? Over.

595
00:56:12.306 --> 00:56:13.428
Come on. Jack!

596
00:56:17.274 --> 00:56:20.144
<i>Okay. calm down buddy. </i>
<i>Help is on the way. </i>

597
00:56:32.656 --> 00:56:33.748
Debbie.

598
00:56:40.763 --> 00:56:44.567
<i>Calling all the clowns.</i>
<i>calling all the clowns. This is Jojo. </i>

599
00:56:44.667 --> 00:56:47.603
<i>Are there any space clowns out there?</i>

600
00:56:47.703 --> 00:56:50.713
Guys. could you stop fooling around?

601
00:56:51.240 --> 00:56:52.632
Look. Mike. come on.

602
00:56:52.732 --> 00:56:56.257
cocoons. popcorn guns.
monster shadows... woo-hoo.

603
00:56:56.357 --> 00:56:59.163
- What do you think we are?
- We're not as stupid as we look.

604
00:56:59.263 --> 00:57:01.931
This isn't the first wild thing you've
tried to pull over on us.

605
00:57:02.031 --> 00:57:03.751
- Look. you remember Hidden Lake?
- Uh-huh.

606
00:57:03.867 --> 00:57:06.671
Oh c'mon. forget Hidden Lake.
This has nothing to do with Hidden Lake.

607
00:57:06.771 --> 00:57:10.237
We would have to be total morons
to believe this clown invasion crap.

608
00:57:10.337 --> 00:57:13.029
If there are killer clowns
runnin' around here.

609
00:57:13.129 --> 00:57:15.188
...then I'm Porky Pig.

610
00:57:34.383 --> 00:57:35.748
Loading zone

611
00:58:08.617 --> 00:58:10.927
We gotta get the hell outta here!

612
00:58:38.251 --> 00:58:39.251
Eww!

613
00:59:30.344 --> 00:59:33.354
<i>- Debbie. It's Mike. Open up. </i>
- Mike?

614
00:59:35.344 --> 00:59:38.004
Debbie...
Debbie...

615
01:00:23.953 --> 01:00:25.621
Okay. see this
white house right over here?

616
01:00:25.721 --> 01:00:27.137
Take a right... I mean. left. Left.

617
01:00:27.237 --> 01:00:28.236
- Left?
- Right.

618
01:00:28.336 --> 01:00:30.646
- Right.
- No. left!

619
01:00:38.734 --> 01:00:41.114
The house's right up.. uh...

620
01:00:42.171 --> 01:00:44.298
Shit. What is that?

621
01:00:51.714 --> 01:00:53.477
Wow... Look at that.

622
01:00:53.616 --> 01:00:54.616
Mike!

623
01:00:56.275 --> 01:00:57.275
Woah!

624
01:01:00.389 --> 01:01:03.399
Come on! We can't lose her!
They got Debbie!

625
01:01:17.173 --> 01:01:18.373
Hey. Mike!

626
01:01:28.017 --> 01:01:30.379
C'mon Rich. we're losing it.
Can't you go a little bit faster?

627
01:01:30.479 --> 01:01:34.531
Come on. Mike. what do you want?
This is an ice cream truck.

628
01:01:46.402 --> 01:01:48.782
Hey Rich. the cops!
Stop the truck!

629
01:01:49.590 --> 01:01:50.799
Woah...

630
01:01:53.309 --> 01:01:54.478
Shit. Rich. now you did it.

631
01:01:54.578 --> 01:01:56.729
I did it?! What do you mean?
You told me to stop.

632
01:01:56.829 --> 01:01:58.392
Didn't I tell you to pull over?

633
01:01:58.492 --> 01:02:00.177
No you didn't.
You said "stop". so I stopped.

634
01:02:00.277 --> 01:02:01.249
Well. I meant "pull over".

635
01:02:01.349 --> 01:02:03.357
If you meant "pull over"
you should've said "pull over".

636
01:02:03.457 --> 01:02:05.244
Why don't you say
what you mean next time?

637
01:02:05.344 --> 01:02:08.144
Come on. let's see what happened.

638
01:02:10.759 --> 01:02:12.090
Dave. are you OK?

639
01:02:13.929 --> 01:02:16.044
God. Oh fuck...

640
01:02:16.144 --> 01:02:18.334
What the hell are you guys doing?

641
01:02:18.434 --> 01:02:19.594
They got Debbie.

642
01:02:21.036 --> 01:02:22.996
Get in the truck now.

643
01:02:25.207 --> 01:02:28.593
Gee. officer. I am really sorry.
I was feelin' a little queasy...

644
01:02:28.693 --> 01:02:30.277
You might wanna tell me
where they're headed.

645
01:02:30.377 --> 01:02:32.963
They went that way. but we're lost.
I don't know where they went.

646
01:02:33.063 --> 01:02:35.630
I do. If you were a clown.
where would you hide?

647
01:02:35.730 --> 01:02:36.899
The amusement park!

648
01:02:36.999 --> 01:02:39.239
- Great!
- Alright!

649
01:03:12.354 --> 01:03:15.784
The park is closed.
I'll have to ask you to leave.

650
01:03:47.523 --> 01:03:50.397
What are you gonna do
with these pies. boys?

651
01:04:40.905 --> 01:04:42.205
Hey!
Heyheyheyhey!

652
01:04:42.305 --> 01:04:44.055
Everybody stick together.

653
01:04:46.982 --> 01:04:48.071
She's gone.

654
01:04:48.684 --> 01:04:49.684
Wow...

655
01:04:49.884 --> 01:04:52.334
Hey you guys. this is weird.

656
01:04:53.489 --> 01:04:57.393
- Look at this stuff.
- Looks like a wad of melted ice cream.

657
01:04:57.493 --> 01:05:00.083
- Yes. but it's not.
- Oh shit.

658
01:05:00.729 --> 01:05:01.729
Yeah.

659
01:05:02.498 --> 01:05:03.624
Come on.

660
01:05:15.054 --> 01:05:16.254
- Hey.
- Sorry

661
01:05:18.914 --> 01:05:21.542
Mike. you take this. Follow me.

662
01:05:21.683 --> 01:05:25.743
Alright. you guys. no fooling around.
Stick together. okay?

663
01:05:26.755 --> 01:05:28.995
What the hell is in here?

664
01:05:38.000 --> 01:05:40.067
Ooooooo-hooooo. Scary.

665
01:05:41.069 --> 01:05:45.269
- Dave. did you call for help?
- Yes. it's on its way.

666
01:05:45.440 --> 01:05:47.325
You told them this is an invasion?

667
01:05:47.425 --> 01:05:50.193
I told them.
but I don't even believe it myself.

668
01:05:50.293 --> 01:05:54.633
Where did they come from?
Why are they here? Why clowns?

669
01:05:55.050 --> 01:05:56.529
They are not clowns.

670
01:05:56.629 --> 01:06:01.590
They are some kind of animals
from another world that look like clowns.

671
01:06:01.690 --> 01:06:02.816
Shit. Dave.

672
01:06:03.091 --> 01:06:07.496
Dave. maybe from the ancient astronauts
who came to earth centuries ago...

673
01:06:07.596 --> 01:06:10.816
...and our idea of clowns
just comes from them.

674
01:06:10.933 --> 01:06:12.864
How come they are not funny?

675
01:06:12.964 --> 01:06:14.853
Maybe they're from a dying planet.

676
01:06:14.953 --> 01:06:17.353
Maybe their sun pooped up
and they need a new place to live.

677
01:06:17.455 --> 01:06:21.443
Maybe they need us for experiments.
for dissection and study.

678
01:06:21.543 --> 01:06:23.643
That means they're intelligent

679
01:06:24.179 --> 01:06:26.064
So why don't they communicate with us?

680
01:06:26.164 --> 01:06:28.964
I mean. talk to us
instead of killing us?

681
01:06:29.218 --> 01:06:34.888
Maybe they're just cruisin' through
the galaxy and stopped here for a bite to eat.

682
01:06:37.526 --> 01:06:41.763
Yeah. Look. everybody.
let's just hold off from the talking. okay?

683
01:06:41.863 --> 01:06:43.963
Let's not give ourselves away.

684
01:06:45.000 --> 01:06:46.637
What are we gonna do when we find them?

685
01:06:46.737 --> 01:06:47.701
Can we kill them?

686
01:06:47.801 --> 01:06:50.282
Yeah.
You shoot them in the nose.

687
01:06:59.948 --> 01:07:01.558
Hey. watch this.

688
01:07:03.452 --> 01:07:04.452
Cool.

689
01:07:29.615 --> 01:07:30.815
Weeew!

690
01:07:31.013 --> 01:07:32.695
- What happened?
- What did you do?

691
01:07:32.795 --> 01:07:34.583
I didn't do anything...

692
01:07:34.683 --> 01:07:39.583
Well. don't touch anything. okay?
This place is probably booby-trapped.

693
01:07:43.892 --> 01:07:47.408
Alright. Now look you guys. stay together.
I don't wanna run around and find you too.

694
01:07:47.508 --> 01:07:49.865
No problem. We can handle it.

695
01:07:49.965 --> 01:07:51.365
Yeah...

696
01:07:53.474 --> 01:07:54.474
Woah!

697
01:07:58.907 --> 01:08:00.807
Alright. let's go.

698
01:08:01.510 --> 01:08:04.946
Where did they go?
Come on. Rich. Paul.

699
01:08:05.547 --> 01:08:08.884
Don't worry about the Terenzi brothers.
They do this all the time.

700
01:08:08.984 --> 01:08:12.904
Those guys are like cats.
They always land on their feet.

701
01:08:17.301 --> 01:08:18.701
Weew...

702
01:08:33.141 --> 01:08:35.041
Are you Debbie's roommates?

703
01:08:35.744 --> 01:08:37.214
Wait a second.

704
01:08:39.247 --> 01:08:40.942
I recognize this place.

705
01:08:42.217 --> 01:08:45.857
This is the tent where
Debbie and I were in. Come on!

706
01:08:53.862 --> 01:08:55.124
Go Mike.

707
01:09:07.876 --> 01:09:10.078
Okay. this is where we were before.

708
01:09:10.178 --> 01:09:12.247
Wow. this is incredible.

709
01:09:12.347 --> 01:09:14.249
Looks like they got the whole town.

710
01:09:14.349 --> 01:09:18.153
We got to find her.
What kind of balloon was she in?

711
01:09:18.253 --> 01:09:19.720
Uh... yellow.

712
01:09:20.589 --> 01:09:22.056
Alright.

713
01:09:36.705 --> 01:09:39.367
- Do you see anything. Mike?
- I don't.

714
01:09:44.579 --> 01:09:46.240
Impossible. Mike.

715
01:09:57.726 --> 01:10:00.786
Shh. Quiet.
Move back.

716
01:10:33.787 --> 01:10:34.787
Ah...

717
01:11:46.601 --> 01:11:49.487
Paul was right. man. They are hungry.
They're gonna eat everybody!

718
01:11:49.587 --> 01:11:51.523
Calm down! Just calm down. alright?

719
01:11:51.623 --> 01:11:55.303
We gotta find Debbie
before it's too late. Alright.

720
01:11:57.212 --> 01:12:00.715
Hey. That's the one.
The yellow balloon. Is she in there?

721
01:12:00.815 --> 01:12:02.940
- Yes. she's in there!
- Debbie!

722
01:12:03.040 --> 01:12:04.368
- She's alive.
- Thank God.

723
01:12:04.468 --> 01:12:07.255
- How the we get her out of here?
- I don't know.

724
01:12:07.355 --> 01:12:09.880
- Careful. Mike.
- Damnit!

725
01:12:09.991 --> 01:12:13.017
Debbie? Honey?
Hang on a second. Mike. Damn!

726
01:12:13.962 --> 01:12:15.964
- Woah! What are you doing?
- Stand back. Mike

727
01:12:16.064 --> 01:12:18.839
- You can't shoot. You could kill her.
- Let's just back off. alright?

728
01:12:18.939 --> 01:12:20.804
Now. just get ready to run.

729
01:12:23.638 --> 01:12:25.062
Are you alright?

730
01:12:28.562 --> 01:12:30.671
- Are you OK?
- Oh yeah.

731
01:12:32.347 --> 01:12:33.615
I couldn't breathe.

732
01:12:33.715 --> 01:12:36.377
Let's get up. Mike. give me a hand.

733
01:12:36.484 --> 01:12:39.221
- Oh God.
- We better get the hell out of here.

734
01:12:39.321 --> 01:12:41.706
Come on. Debbie. Come on.

735
01:12:41.806 --> 01:12:43.406
Come on.

